      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hollandaise splits when the emulsion breaks, usually because the heat gets too high or the egg yolks are over-whipped, causing the fat to separate from the water-based yolk. You can try to save it by whisking in a splash of cold water or lemon juice to cool it down and re-stabilize the emulsion, though if it's too greasy, you might need to start fresh. If you're feeling adventurous, you can also try adding a bit of cornstarch slurry to thicken it back up, but be careful not to over-thicken or it will become gummy. Always remember to keep your heat low and whisk constantly to prevent this from happening again next time.",
